--- ## Content Intelligence Pipeline
--- Watch for interesting AI engineering content, analyze, extract lessons, compound.
--- Trigger: manual (`/demerzel reflect <url>`) or scheduled (daily scan of bookmarks)

--- ## Phase 1: INGEST
--- Fetch content and extract metadata.
source content_url
  → fetch(url, format: "markdown")
  → extract_metadata(author, date, platform, topic, engagement_metrics)

--- ## Phase 2: ANALYZE
--- Classify relevance across six domains. Skip if relevance < 0.6.
  → classify_relevance(
      domains: ["claude-code", "ai-agents", "governance", "devops", "ml-ops", "music-tech"],
      threshold: 0.6
    )
  → when relevance < 0.6: log("Low relevance, skip") → conclude F "Not relevant"

--- ## Phase 3: CROSS-REFERENCE
--- Compare with our ecosystem to find gaps, validations, and adoptable techniques.
  → compare_with_demerzel(
      check: [
        "What does the author do that we don't?",
        "What do we do that the author doesn't?",
        "What claims can we validate or refute from experience?",
        "What specific technique should we adopt?"
      ],
      artifacts: context_engine.query(content.topics)  -- uses #163 when available
    )

--- ## Phase 4: EXTRACT Actionable Insights
--- Structured extraction with ERGOL/LOLLI check:
--- - **Agree**: where we violently agree (with citation)
--- - **Learn**: what we should steal (specific, actionable)
--- - **Teach**: what we could teach them (from our experience)
--- - **Challenge**: what we'd push back on (with evidence)
--- - **ERGOL check**: proven in practice or unvalidated?
  → extract_insights(
      format: {
        agree: "Where we violently agree (with citation)",
        learn: "What we should steal (specific, actionable)",
        teach: "What we could teach them (from our experience)",
        challenge: "What we'd push back on (with evidence)",
        ergol_check: "Is this ERGOL (proven in practice) or LOLLI (sounds good, unvalidated)?"
      }
    )

--- ## Phase 5: BS CHECK
--- Apply specificity, falsifiability, density, and commitment tests to key claims.
  → bs_detect(
      tests: [specificity, falsifiability, density, commitment],
      on_claims: content.key_claims
    )

--- ## Phase 6: COMPOUND
--- Actionable insights become GitHub issues. Challenges become draft responses.
  → when insights.learn.length > 0:
      create_issue(
        title: "learn: {insight.summary}",
        body: insights.learn,
        labels: ["continuous-learning"]
      )
  → when insights.challenge.length > 0:
      draft_response(
        platform: content.platform,
        tone: "constructive, specific, evidence-based",
        include: [our_experience, our_data, links_to_demerzel]
      )
  → compound:
      log_to evolution("content-intelligence")
      update department_weights(content.domains)
      when novel_technique: create_skill_candidate(insights.learn)
      post_summary(discord, channel: "research")
